title: American rescued after more than a week in the depths of a Turkish cave
description: American cave explorer Mark Dickey has been rescued from a deep cave in Turkey after he became ill during an expedition roughly nine days ago and was unable to reach the surface.

title: Finding Black joy in unexpected venues: Jam band shows
description: More Black people are finding community when following their favorite jam bands, including groups like Grateful Dead, Dave Matthews Band and Phish.

title: Hunt for escaped Pennsylvania killer has entered the 'long game,' police say
description: Police have entered the "long game" in their hunt for an escaped murderer in Pennsylvania, officials said Monday, as they searched an area where the fleeing prisoner had dumped a stolen van.

title: Danny Masterson rape victim says he got a fair sentence: 'Seems like justice to me'
description: LOS ANGELES — One of the two women “That ’70s Show” star Danny Masterson was convicted of raping told NBC News on Monday that the 30 years to life sentence the judge imposed on the actor “seemed like justice to me.”

title: FDA clears new Covid boosters for people 5 and older

title: State election chiefs look to courts to deal with Trump ballot challenges
description: State election officers have a near-unified message about challenges to Donald Trump’s eligibility for the ballot in 2024: We want nothing to do with this.

title: Maternity ward to close as family calls for justice in death of Black mother
description: Centinela hospital in Inglewood, California, will close its maternity ward later this month after the family of a Black woman who died in labor sued.

title: U.S. marks 22 years since the 9/11 terror attacks
description: Americans marked the anniversary of the 9/11 terror attacks in commemoration ceremonies at the sites where nearly 3,000 Americans lost their lives. NBC News' Rehema Ellis reports on the services at Ground Zero in New York and the continued efforts to identify the remains of victims.

title: Disney, Charter deal to end blackout includes streaming discount for cable subscribers
description: The blackout fight between cable giant Charter Communications and Disney is over.

description: The biggest tech monopoly trial since the Department of Justice challenged Microsoft more than 20 years ago is set to begin on Tuesday, kicking off a new chapter of anti-monopoly enforcement in the U.S.
